title: How to search for a book in the iPad or Cataloguer bookshelves
media:
---
<div>
<h1>How do I search for a book in the iPad or Cataloguer bookshelves?</h1>
<p>Crash data is sent automatically by Apple, <b>if you have enabled sharing analytics</b>.</p>

To enable sharing analytics on iPad/iPhone iOS 11.3.1, in the Settings app:
<ol>
<li>Select the iPad bookshelf (or any of those under Cataloguer)</li>
<li>In the middle of the screen, swipe downwards with one finger</li>
<li>A search box appears</li>
<li>Type in the <b>phrase</b> you wish to search for</li>
<li>The phrase is searched for (insensitively) in the Title, Authors, and Subjects fields</li>

<h3>Note that the search is for an exact string, not the individual words in the string.</h3>
</ol>
</div>
